<item>
            <title>[LU-13981] tests should be consistent in use of &quot;truncate&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13981</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some tests uses $TRUNCATE to truncate a file.&#160; This explicitly find .../lustre/tests/truncate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other tests use &quot;truncate&quot; and assume it is the same program.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One test (sanity 399b) uses &quot;truncate -s&quot;, which assumes /usr/bin/truncate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not really sure how all this works... test_399b fails for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tests should be consistent in which truncate program is used, and how it is called.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
